  "original_title": "Sri Lanka schedules daily one-hour power cut from September 06 to 09",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka schedules daily one-hour power cut from September 06 to 09",
      "author": "Dulya de Silva",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka will experience up to one hour of power cuts from Tuesday September 06 to Friday September 09 September, Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission (PUCSL) Janaka Ratnayake said.",
        "All groups A, B, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, P, Q, R, S, T, U, V and W will have a one-hour of power cut between 6.00 pm to 9.00 pm.",
        "The state-run Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB) announced that power cuts would only take place after 6.00 pm on Monday.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s power cut durations had to be increased slightly to to a sudden breakdown in the island\u2019s Norochcholai power plant, and the unavailability of fuel. The outage duration was\u00a0rolled back due to the availability of hydroelectricity with the heavy rains, but the fuel situation remains the same, a spokesperson from the CEB told EconomyNext.",
        "The Ceylon Petroleum Corporation previously released a statement saying that there was an adequate supply of all fuels both imported and refined within the country, after fuel queues were reported once again in some areas. (Colombo/Sep05/2022)"
      ],
